follow the directions. With recipes. (Norris, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.BRUSSELS-SPROUTS _ Be honest. Did anyone ever look at the
Thanksgiving table and say ``Oh, goody! Brussels sprouts!'' But as
sure as turkey is the main course, it's guaranteed that November
food magazines will have pictures of the bird surrounded by little
green Brussels sprouts. Brussels sprouts seem suited to the season.
(Heller, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SPROUTS-TIPS _ Tips on buying Brussels sprouts. (Dayton Daily
News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WINE-COLUMN _ With all this millennium hoopla, you'd think some
savvy wine marketer would have come up with a way to slap ``Vintage
2000'' on the label of their new bottling. Without a time machine,
though, that's not quite feasible. Even with today's technology, it
still takes time to pick the grapes, crush 'em, ferment the juice
and bottle it. Not much time, mind you. That's why you'll have no
problem saying goodbye to 1999 with a glass of 1999 vintage wine in
your hand _ if you're so inclined. (Fisher, Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
