<HEADLINE>
KANSAS CITY STAR BUDGET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Thursday,
Nov. 18. If you have any questions, please call The Star's News
Desk at (816) 234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   ACCRED: U.S. District Judge Dean Whipple should issue his
decision Wednesday on whether the KC School District loses its
accreditation. With reaction from the school board, parents,
teachers etc. Phil O'Connor, Kevin Hoffmann.
</P>
<P>
   SICK: (tent.) An 8-year-old Independence, Mo., girl died of
asthma last week after being told by Truman Medical Center East to
wait two weeks for an appointment where an emergency inhaler could
be prescribed. Advocates for the poor say the girl, who was
uninsured, was a victim of a two-tiered health system where the
poor must wait for the care they need. When her symptoms worsened,
she died on the way to an Independence hospital. Photo. John
Martellaro. 25-30.
</P>
<P>
   STOWERS _ The administrative offices of the Stowers Institute of
Medical Research opens on Thurday. We assess its potential economic
impact. Julius Karash. Photo. Graphic.
</P>
