</P>
<P>
   KITNA. Jon Kitna's round, beefy face and crewcut make him a dead
ringer for a letter sweater-wearing football player of the 1950s.
He's the guy who jumps off the page as a jock in everybody's high
school or college yearbook. He's a success story from a different
era, too, when a college player with NFL potential could be
ignored. The Kurt Warners and Damon Huards were merely misevaluated
by NFL scouts. Kitna, the NFL's fifth-rated passer and who's helped
lead the Seattle Seahawks into first place, was flat-out ignored.
Jonathan Rand. 25.
</P>
