remastered, $29.95 VHS, $39.95 DVD.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Brigitte Bardot: ``And God Created Woman,'' uncut 95-minute
version available for the first time on video, and ``The Night
Heaven Fell,'' $19.95 each.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Jean Cocteau: ``Blood of a Poet,'' ``Orpheus'' and ``Testament
of Orpheus,'' $29.95 each, VHS.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Kids: ``Bartok the Magnificent,'' further adventures of the
white bat sidekick from ``Anastasia,'' $19.98 VHS, $29.98 DVD.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  National Geographic: ``Mysteries of Egypt,'' ``The Noble
Horse,'' $19.98.
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
