   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-PILOT (Washington) _ As Egyptian officials begin arriving
to review and examine the evidence, investigators identify the
words and movements of a backup copilot whom they suspect
deliberately sent EgyptAir Flight 990 into a suicide dive. By
Thomas Farragher and Ann Scales. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-EGYPT (Cairo) _ Those who knew veteran pilot Gamil El
Batouty lash out at suggestions he may have deliberately flown
Flight 990 into the ocean. By Charles M. Sennott. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-ISLAM (Undated) _ As the crash investigation continues,
Muslims worry that once again people will quickly -- and wrongly --
conclude that there is a link between Islam and fanaticism. By
Joanna Weiss. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   BISHOPS-COLLEGES (Washington) _ Bucking warnings that it would
create ``disaster'' for the church and dissent on US campuses, the
nation's Catholic bishops overwhelmingly approve a landmark
document tightening their authority over 236 Catholic colleges. By
Kate Zernike. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   THALIDOMIDE-MYELOMA (Undated) _ Researchers say thalidomide,
banned after causing birth defects four decades ago, can produce
dramatic results in treating myeloma, a bone-marrow cancer that
strikes nearly 14,000 Americans annually. By Judy Foreman. 850
words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-SPANK (Boston) _ Court rules that a minister did not abuse
his son when he spanked him with a belt and the Department of
Social Services was wrong to label him a child abuser. By John
Ellement. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HANCOCK-DEMUTUALIZE (Boston) _ Hearing on John Hancock's plan to
convert to a publicly traded company produces expected fireworks.
By Lynnley Browning. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-CAVS-CELTICS (Boston) _ By Peter May.
</P>
<P>
   w/
