   TEXAS-DEFENSE-GOP leaders hailed Wednesday a $13 defense
spending bill for reforming the energy department's chain of
command and boosting retirement benefits and payrolls for the
military. Rep. Mac Thornberry, R-Amarillo, acclaimed the bill's
creation of a semi-autonomous office within the Energy Department
to handle nuclear weapons. The House will likely vote on the bill
tomorrow. (500 words.) By Alex Canizares
</P>
