<P>
   Gear.com: www.gear.com/ _ This store sells brand-name sporting
gear from specialty companies, including Bolle, the North Face,
Swiss Army, Fila, Wilson, Rossignol and Timberland.
</P>
<P>
   Nike: www.nike.com/store _ Clothes, watches, sunglasses,
backpacks, Michael Jordan's line, and, of course, footwear for
every sport, including walking.
</P>
<P>
   Shop Sports: www.shopsports.com/ _ In addition to sports
clothing and gear, this store has a place for fans to shop for team
clothing and collectibles, videos and books, fitness equipment,
software and vitamins. There is even a page to buy balls for almost
every sport.
</P>
<P>
   ELECTRONICS
</P>
<P>
   AAAnet: www.aaanet-inc.com/ _ This online mall sells a range of
cameras from 35mm SLR to digital cameras, from such manufacturers
as Canon, Pentax, Sony, Minolta and Sharp. There are also
telescopes, binoculars and watches.
</P>
<P>
   Consumer Direct: www.consumer-direct.com/ _ Consumer Direct
sells DVD players, high-definition and projection televisions,
telephones, audio components, VCRs and universal remotes. The site
is simple but has detailed specifications on each product.
</P>
<P>
   HiFi.com: www7.hifi.com/consumer/default.asp _ The site
specializes in audio components; portable devices like CD players,
camcorders and speakers; televisions and satellite dishes and
computer-related items like sound and video cards, DVD players,
speakers and WebTV.
</P>
<P>
   Netmarket: www.netmarket.com/ _ This site offers home
electronics as well as books, computers, fashions, toys and home
furnishings. It carries a range of electronics, including digital
and video cameras, fax machines, telephones, shredders and minidisc
players, and there are helpful buyers guides for products.
</P>
<P>
   GAMES
</P>
<P>
   CNET's Game Center: www.gamecenter.com/?tag(EQ)st.cn.1-ron.sb.gc
_ The game center features reviews, cheats, news and downloads. It
also has a feature called shopper, where buyers can find games
through the manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
   Egames: www.egames.com/egames2/ _ The site offers computer games
in several family-friendly categories, including arcade, cards,
shoot-em-ups, strategy games and games for girls.
</P>
<P>
   Player's Choice: www.playersc.com/ _ Player's Choice is one of
several stores nationwide that offer new and used video games,
dating back to those for the Atari 2600 system (Asteroids, Pacman,
Super Breakout). Player's Choice also has game news, a history of
the video game, tips and cheats, and a list of the top 100 games as
voted on by its customers (Pokemon is already No. 5).
</P>
<P>
   KB Kids: www.kbkids.com/ _ KB Kids is among many toy stores
online that carry computer games and video games, those for
Playstation, Dreamcast, Nintendo and handheld players like NeoGeo
and Game Boy. KB Kids, like the others, also sells the consoles and
the accessories.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC CDs
</P>
<P>
   All Music Guide (http://allmusic.com/ _ Customers cannot buy
music CDs at All Music Guide, but it is an excellent site for
finding a particular CD or other releases. Music can be searched by
artist, album, song, style or label, and once an album is found,
there is a list of songs, a biography of the artist, credits and
reviews.
</P>
<P>
   CD Now: www.cdnow.com/ _ CD Now features contemporary music and
old recordings on compact discs, with reviews, interviews and
excerpts that can be heard online. There are versions of the site
in seven languages other than English.
</P>
<P>
   CD World: cdworld.com/ _ The site sells music and sheet music,
as well as videos, software, hardware and video games.
</P>
<P>
   Columbia House: www.columbiahouse.com _ The onetime record club,
which once lured customers with offers like ``get seven albums for
one cent,'' is online with music, videos, DVD films and software.
