<P>
   SPEND-CONGRESS (Washington) _ The White House and Republican
leaders in Congress, grappling for political advantage, agreed in
principle to an across-the-board spending cut of about $1.3
billion, and met Wednesday afternoon to seal a final budget deal.
By Tim Weiner.
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-TALKS (Belfast, Northern Ireland) _ The Irish
Republican Army said Wednesday that it ``unequivocally'' backed the
Northern Ireland peace agreement, and it agreed to appoint a
go-between to the commission charged with bringing about
paramilitary disarmament. The eagerly awaited statement For the
first time in its history, the outlawed, secret paramilitary force
showed a willingness to consider the dismantling of its arsenal, a
taboo subject it has traditionally associated with surrender. By
Warren Hoge.
