<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, Nov. 18. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
AMWEST (Phoenix) - America West, the worst on-time of the 10 major
airlines, continues to be plauged by operations problems with a
rash of cancellations delaying thousands passengers. That's bad
news for travelers heading into the Thanksgiving holiday travel
period, busiest of the year. Reports indicated that the FAA has
cracked down on the airline and is no longer granting extensions on
scheduled maintenance, which has forced planes to be taken out of
service. As a result, hundreds of flights have been canceled over
the past few weeks. By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in the ``A''
and ``F'' categories. &QL; 
