<P>
   DOMESTIC-PARTNERS (Los Angeles) -- Calling it a civil rights
issue, the Los Angeles City Council on Wednesday broadened its own
requirements on benefits for domestic partners to include companies
that do business with the city. Under the draft ordinance approved
12-0, municipal contractors that offer benefits to workers and
their spouses will be required also to make benefits available to
those in partnership relationships. A survey of businesses showed
the costs would be about $2,100 per worker per year. By Beth
Barrett. (Will move on the ``n'' California news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   EXPELLED-UNIVERSITY (Los Angeles) -- The Cal State University
system announced Tuesday that 1,440 out of 19,237 freshmen who
needed to take remedial classes were expelled. The figures provide
the first comprehensive look at how Executive Order 665 has
affected students throughout the state. By Robert Monroe. (Will
move on the ``n'' California news wire.)
</P>
<P>
