<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Where to get hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to
help you locate it. But due to the volume of mail, we cannot track
down every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the
column will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag.
Write us at Buyer's Edge Find It, Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at
buyersedge(at)ajc.com (please include your name, the city you live
in and daytime phone number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Could you please find Vicks inhaler stick for me? I can't use
the liquid inhalers.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sharon Dolensek, Lilburn, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: You can exhale. We found your Vicks Vapor Inhaler at Eckerds,
2480 Briarcliff Road N.E. (404-321-4250) One tube is $3.99.
According to a spokesman, there had been production problems with
the inhaler and it temporarily disappeared from store shelves. But
these problems have been straightened out. The inhaler, according
to the manufacturer, provides relief from nasal congestion due to
colds, hay fever, allergies and sinusitis by shrinking swollen
membranes.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I understand it might be possible to purchase clothing for
women who have physical conditions relating to osteoporosis, for
example, a curving of the back. I feel a lot of people might want
to know about these specially constructed garments.
</P>
<P>
   _ Janet F. Miller, Douglasville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: For an answer, we went right to the source, the National
Osteoporosis Foundation in Washington. Spokeswoman Molly
Natchipolsky says that, so far, no manufacturer makes clothes
specifically for those who suffer from the disease, which causes
compression fractures of the spine. These fractures can cause body
changes: a loss of height, curving of the shoulders and back, a
thickening waistline.
</P>
<P>
   However, the foundation has a booklet, ``Style Wise: A Fashion
Guide for Women With Osteoporosis'' ($2.75 including shipping),
that gives fashion and design tips. The booklet, done in
partnership with the New York's Fashion Institute of Technology,
offers advice on silhouettes, colors and accessories. Sometimes a
simple fix, such as inserting shoulder pads in tops or dresses,
will give immediate balance to sloping shoulders and provide the
illusion of a straighter back and smaller waist. To get the
booklet, send check or money order to: STYL 99, P.O. Box 96616,
Washington, DC 20077-7456.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Aussie Unscented Sprunch Spray. I was last
able to buy it at Target in Lawrenceville. When I went last week,
it was gone and was told the store would probably not have it
anymore. I am almost out. Help.
</P>
<P>
   _ Monica
</P>
<P>
   S. Keller, Winder, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Like many companies, Aussie has repackaged and reformulated
some of its products. The bottles are now the color of eggplant
with a magenta logo and might have been off shelves for a short
time while this was done. We found Aussie Unscented Sprunch Spray
(12-ounce bottle, $4.29) at CVS, 2910 Buford Highway N.E.
(404-325-2735). The spray, which provides hold without stickiness
or flaking, now contains Australian Paw Flower, to add shine and
softness to the hair.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Could you help me find Gillette Regular Lather Shave Cream
for my husband Irving who's used it for years? He'd be very
grateful.
</P>
<P>
   _ Helena Schussheim, Decatur, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Brusha, brusha, brusha. According to a company spokeswoman,
few stores stock this product because very few men still use
shaving brushes. However, this lather shave cream, for men who
still use a brush when they shave, is available at Drug Emporium,
2625 Piedmont Road N.E. (404-233-1201). A 4.5-ounce tube is $2.29.
And Gillette's brushless shave cream is also $2.29, at the same
location.
</P>
<P>
   Q: About six weeks ago, I moved to Atlanta from Columbus, Ohio.
After eating most meals in restaurants, my favorite item on any
menu is anything with applewood smoked bacon. It's delicious!
However, I went to Publix, Kroger and Harry's Farmers Market and
didn't see any. Can you tell me where to get it?
</P>
<P>
   _ Mari Lappin, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Soon, you will be able to bring home the bacon. Literally. We
found a 1-pound package of Applewood Smoked Bacon ($6.49) at
eatZi's, 3221 Peachtree Road N.E. (404-237-2266). North Country
Smokehouse in Claremont, N.H., smokes its thick-sliced bacon with
applewood and cures it with maple syrup, says fourth generation
owner/butcher Mike Satzow. Visit the company's Web site at
www.ncsmokehouse.com. Or call 1-800-258-4304.
</P>
<P>
   Another company in Wisconsin, Nueske's Hillcrest Farm, also
smokes it bacon with applewood but cures it with brown sugar and
honey for a sweet smoky flavor. Look for it on the Web at
www.nueske.com. Or call 1-800-392-2266.
</P>
<P>
   Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
