<DATE_TIME> 1999-11-17 20:51 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3041 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f BC-NICKLAUS-COURSE18-COX     11-17 0477
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NICKLAUS-COURSE18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Nicklaus plans specialty golf course in Georgia
 &HT;    By Andrew Meadows
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Legendary golfer Jack Nicklaus plans to develop a
``Bear's Best'' golf course in Gwinnett County that has a layout
mirroring 18 of his favorite hole designs.
</P>
<P>
   Nicklaus' golf development company, Golden Bear International,
is partnering with Dallas-based ClubCorp Inc. on the 574-acre
development along the banks of the Chattahoochee River off Settles
Bridge Road near Suwanee, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   As part of the deal, Pulte Home Corp. plans to build about 500
homes at the development, which will be called Edinburgh. The homes
will range from $250,000 to $1 million. Construction is to begin
next year with a fall 2001 completion date.
</P>
<P>
   The course will draw its holes from more than 150
Nicklaus-designed courses, including Muirfield Village, Shoal Creek
and Castle Pines. The golf course concept, called ``Bear's Best,''
is one of two being developed in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   Jim Hinckley, president and chief operating officer of ClubCorp,
said the hole replications will be virtually exact, down to the
slope of the fairways and the size and shape of the sand traps.
</P>
<P>
   The development will also feature a driving range and golf
teaching academy.
</P>
<P>
   According to Smart Numbers, a home sales research firm, the
Suwanee area is one of the hottest housing markets in the Atlanta
region. Smart Numbers reported that Suwanee ZIP code experienced
the most new home sales of any metro Atlanta ZIP code outside
Interstate 285.
</P>
<P>
   In 1998, 1,272 new homes were sold in the 30024 ZIP code, a 12.6
percent increase. The average cost of the homes was $234,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We picked Atlanta because we feel it is one of the strongest
markets,'' ClubCorp's Hinckley said. ``It also has a strong
corporate presence.''
</P>
<P>
   Dave Richey, ClubCorp's vice president for development, said the
development's housing permits already have been issued, and he
expects the golf course component to be permitted soon.
</P>
<P>
   ClubCorp is one of the world's largest owners and operators of
golf courses. The privately held company owns and operates more
than 200 golf clubs, including Pinehurst Resort and Country Club,
the site of this year's U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
   The Suwanee development is the first Bear's Best design. It is
being built simultaneously with a course in Las Vegas. ClubCorp and
Golden Bear are negotiating to build two more similar-themed
courses in Washington, D.C. and Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   In 1998, the ClubCorp inked a deal with Nicklaus to develop
several courses. The partnership is developing BirchRiver on the
Chestatee River in Dahlonega. The course is to open next year.
Nicklaus also designed the Golden Bear Golf Club at Laurel Spring
in Forsyth County.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-17-99 2051EST &QL; 
