<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ten honored as Best Accessorized Celebrities
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Do you believe in the power of
accessories?
</P>
<P>
   Cher apparently does. The Accessories Council named the
flamboyant diva one of this year's Best Accessorized Celebrities.
</P>
<P>
   The 10 well-heeled women on the list ``understand the value of
accessories and have promoted them in both their personal and
professional lives,'' says Sheila Block, executive director of the
council. ``Accessories help us define our own sense of personal
style.''
</P>
<P>
   The rest of the Best looks like this: TV newswomen Katie Couric
and Barbara Walters; New York socialite Blaine Trump; songstress
Lauryn Hill; Oscar winner Gwyneth Paltrow; and mega-kilowatt
actresses Cameron Diaz, Nicole Kidman, Julia Roberts and Sharon
Stone.
</P>
<P>
   At the council's third annual awards earlier this month, the
following also were announced:
</P>
<P>
   Best Visual Merchandising in an Accessory Department _ Saks
Fifth Avenue
</P>
<P>
   Company with Best Accessory Advertising Campaign _ Kenneth Cole
</P>
<P>
   Best Coverage of Accessories by a Consumer Fashion Magazine _ In
Style
</P>
<P>
   Best Accessories Licensed Program _ Ralph Lauren
</P>
<P>
   Best Accessories Designer _ Kate Spade
</P>
<P>
   The top prize, the Accessories Council of Excellence Award, went
to ``Another World'' actress Linda Dano. Previous winners include
Joan Rivers and Kathie Lee Gifford.
</P>
<P>
   The nonprofit Accessories Council was formed four years ago to
raise awareness of the $25 billion business in jewelry, handbags,
belts, shoes and other accessory items.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
