<SLUG> BC-KFC18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Company buys four KFC restaurants
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ JFS International Inc., a Lithonia, Ga.-based KFC
Corp. franchisee, has consolidated its operations in Georgia by
buying four restaurants. The four newly acquired units in Georgia
bring the number of JFS holdings to eight. Beth Redford, a KFC
spokeswoman, said the owners of JFS, Milton and Judy Sanders, sold
three restaurants in West Virginia and Ohio. They then bought four
company-owned units on Bankhead Highway, Austell Road, Canton Road
and Powder Springs Road. The Sanderses are part of a partnership of
other minority owners that operate 11 KFC restaurants in Knoxville,
Tenn. Redford said KFC Corp., a unit of Tricon Global Restaurants
Inc., based in Louisville, Ky., plans to sell 200 company-owned
stores next year. An undetermined number are in Georgia. Minority
franchisees will be given the opportunity to make first offers on a
fourth of those restaurants.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
