</P>
<P>
   Channel 2, 12:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   You don't really need to know much more than that _ except the
Gators might be the most unimpressive third-ranked team in the
country in a long time. They don't even know who'll play
quarterback because neither has impressed.
</P>
<P>
   No. 8 Alabama at Auburn
</P>
<P>
   ESPN, 4:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Somehow, Auburn (5-5, 2-5 SEC) needs one more win to become bowl
eligible. How'd that happen? Because QB Ben Leard has been passing
at a 72 percent clip, with 50 of his 85 completions going to WR
Ronney Daniels. The game's at Auburn's Jordan-Hare Stadium, where
the Tide is 0-4 in meetings there.
</P>
