<HEADLINE>
HOUSE OF LLOYD IS SOLD TO NEW YORK INVESTMENT GROUP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RICK ALM  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (Undated) Privately held House of Lloyd Inc. in Grandview, Mo.,
has been sold for an undisclosed price to a New York investment
group that has similar retail holdings.
</P>
<P>
   Proceeds of the sale by the Harry J. Lloyd Charitable Trust are
to benefit hundreds of Christian evangelism groups, charities and
medical research projects worldwide.
</P>
<P>
   The new owner is a partnership made up of Kier Group Holdings
LLC, a New York investment firm, and SG Capital Partners, an
American affiliate of France's Societe Generale, one of the world's
largest banks.
</P>
<P>
   The House of Lloyd's chief executive, Demi Lloyd, will step
down, and Kier Group Chairman Joel Kier, 35, will assume the titles
of chairman and chief executive.
</P>
<P>
   Kier said Wednesday that the company's 1,000 seasonal and
full-time workers in Grandview were assured of their jobs and that
he expected expansion.
</P>
<P>
   ``We invested in the business and the people there who are in
place,'' Kier said. ``We gave them that message in a meeting today.
We encouraged all of them to stay with us.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a business that has extreme potential to grow in a
robust industry that brings a retail shopping experience into the
customer's home.''
</P>
<P>
   Founder Henry Lloyd died in 1997, and federal charitable trust
tax laws mandated the company's sale within five years.
</P>
<P>
   Demi Lloyd said her departure marked the end of the Lloyd
family's direct involvement in operations of the 47-year-old
worldwide marketer of giftware, Christmas decor, and home and
kitchen wares.
</P>
<P>
   Lloyd said of the sale decision: ``There were some emotions
involved. My sister (Jami Kay) and I considered purchasing the
company, but we don't have the resources for such an acquisition.
</P>
<P>
   ``My family is proud that the company Dad founded and nurtured
is in good hands.''
</P>
<P>
   Lloyd said she would stay at home and raise her children, ages 1
and 2.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the mom job will be more challenging'' than being
chief executive of a worldwide company with offices in Mexico,
Europe and Puerto Rico, she said.
</P>
<P>
   The sale proceeds are to be distributed by the Lloyd trust to
various religious and medical research groups. The Loch Lloyd
Country Club will remain part of the trust.
</P>
<P>
   At the House of Lloyd, the catalog offers many religious items
and features photos of Demi Lloyd and district manager Carie White
and their families. In a message to customers, Lloyd wrote in one
catalog about her father's faith and said his company was a
``business that enables people to put their families first ...
(and) is dedicated to bringing joy and meaning to life.''
</P>
<P>
   Kier pledged that those values would continue.
</P>
<P>
   ``The culture and the traditions of the business are very
important with any company, and with this one in particular,'' he
said. ``We think Christian and home values are an important concept
that we want to nurture and build.''
</P>
<P>
   The House of Lloyd does not disclose sales figures, but Demi
Lloyd said the company filled about half a million orders annually.
Most of those sales are made through 30,000 representatives who
stage home parties and demonstrate the products.
</P>
<P>
   ``The House of Lloyd has a terrific name and legacy behind that
name,'' Kier said. ``We are absolutely committed to (maintaining)
that name.''
</P>
<P>
   The Kier group owns other collectible, giftware and candle
firms, including Ceratech Inc., Papel Giftware Inc., Fitz and Floyd
Inc. and Flintlock Ltd. Kier also has interests in Bell Sports Inc.
and a home cleaning products firm.
</P>
<P>
   Kier previously was a senior executive at Edizione Holdings SpA,
the primary holding company for the Italian Benetton family's
interests in the worldwide sporting goods industry.
</P>
<P>
   Kier lives in New York with his wife and daughter and is active
in wildlife conservation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
